<h4>Web Beacons</h4>
<p>We may use technologies called technologies called Web Beacons that communicate information from your browser to our web server. Web Beacons are tiny graphics with unique identifiers, similar in function to cookies, and are used to track the online movements of Web users. Web Beacons can be embedded in web pages, videos, or emails, and can allow a web server to read certain types of information from your browser, check whether you have viewed a particular web page or email message, and determine, among other things, the time and date on which you view the Web Beacon, the IP of your computer, and the URL of the web page from which the Web Beacon was viewed. These Web Beacons may be used for a variety of purposes, including to analyze the use of the Services in conjunction with cookies to provide content and ads that are more relevant to you.</p>
<h4>Log Files</h4>
<p>&nbsp;Similar to most other websites accessible via a web server, we collect and store footprints of user traffic activity in flat files called log files. This information includes Internet Protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, referring/exit pages, operating system and date/time stamp. We use this data as aggregated information to observe and analyze trends, and subsequently to serve the Website to the demographic users in a better fashion.</p>
